<body><p>GE.14-12680 
</p>
<p>*1412680* 
</p>
<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Twenty-fifth session 
</b>Agenda item 3 
<b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, civil, 
political, economic, social and cultural rights, 
including the right to development 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Algeria, Bahrain,<footnote name="*">Non-member State of the Human Rights Council.  </footnote> Russian Federation, South Africa, United Arab Emirates: 
amendment to draft resolution A/HRC/25/L.18/Rev.1 
</b></p>
<p><b>  25/&#8230;  Adequate housing as a component of the right to an adequate 
standard of living 
</b></p>
<p>After paragraph 2, insert a new paragraph <i>reading</i>  
</p>
<p>2 bis. <i>Reaffirms</i> that each State should undertake to take steps, individually and 
through international assistance and cooperation, especially economic and technical, to the 
maximum of its available resources with a view to achieving progressively the full 
realization of economic, social and cultural rights, including the right to adequate housing 
as a component of the right to an adequate standard of living,  
</p>
<p>    
</p>
<p>  
